title: Structure of the cross section of the photoneutron reaction on the Pb-208 nucleus in the region of the giant dipole resonance.

x4freetext: Structure  of the cross section  of  the  photoneutron
reaction on the Pb-208 nucleus in the region  of  the
giant dipole resonance.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Soviet Journal of Nuclear Physics, Vol.12, p.370 (1971)

x4freetext: - Eng.trans.of YF,12,682,1270
The multichannel method  of the reaction yield
measurement was  used  in  which  the  bremmstrahlung
end-point  energy  has  been changed automatically in
each cycle of electron acceleration in betatron  with
50 Hz frequency.
The water sample was used as the target.
The  Penfold - Leiss  unfolding   method   with
the bin 200 keV was used for obtaining cross  section
data from experimental yield curve.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Mean root-square errors are given.
The data have been digitized in the CDFE.
The  cross  section  is   obtained  for  the  reaction
82-Pb-208(gamma,xn) at  the  excitation energies
7.3-17.3 MeV. In the cross section there is a number
of maxima with 200-400 keV widths.
